OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1773662584
OL,3,CTrump steps up pressure on allies over
OL,4,CStrait of Hormuz as strikes continue
OL,6,FUS President Donald Trump has stepped
OL,7,Fup pressure on allies, demanding
OL,8,Fcountries, including the UK, send
OL,9,Fwarships to keep the Strait of Hormuz
OL,10,Fopen, as Iranian strikes continued on
OL,11,FGulf countries.
OL,13,FOver the weekend, Sir Keir Starmer and
OL,14,FTrump discussed the importance of
OL,15,Freopening a key shipping route in the
OL,16,FMiddle East during their first
OL,17,Fconversation since the US president
OL,18,Fcalled for Britain to send warships to
OL,19,Fthe Strait of Hormuz.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1773662584
OL,3,CTrump steps up pressure on allies over
OL,4,CStrait of Hormuz as strikes continue
OL,6,FStarmer on Sunday did not heed calls
OL,7,Ffrom Trump to deploy warships;
OL,8,Finstead, Britain is currently mulling
OL,9,Fover the possibility of sending mine-
OL,10,Fhunting drones to the region amid
OL,11,Fworries of an Iranian build-up of
OL,12,Fexplosives in the narrow sea passage.
OL,14,FThe US president said Nato faces a
OL,15,F"very bad" future should its member
OL,16,Fstates fail to help, adding: "We'll
OL,17,Fsee if they help us. Because I've long
OL,18,Fsaid that we'll be there for them, but
OL,19,Fthey won't be there for us."
